just_use rb_swap.go

# label: INTRICATE
# role: encodes domain knowledge

The "substitute trick": kick a same-value, same-color, different-suit card
out of an rb (red/black alternating) run, slot the hand card into its
seat. Constraints:

- Post-substitution stack must still classify as RedBlackRun (color
  alternation preserved).
- Kicked card must find a home: a not-yet-full (<4) same-value SET that
  doesn't already have its suit, or a PureRun that accepts it at an end.

Steve's vocabulary: see feedback_lynrummy_trick_vocab — "substitute trick"
in conversation, rb_swap / RbSwap in code. If no home exists for the
kicked card the play is suppressed entirely.
